{
  "texts": [
    "While GPU memory gets allocated, GPU compute effectively stalls, waiting for data to process.",
    "This was measured through xctrace and visualized with Apple Instruments application.",
    "Impact of QuantizationA prominent method for reducing the memory traffic between main and on-chip memory is to decrease the precision of the weights and activations of the Neural Network [32,61,110].",
    "However, this often comes at the expense of model accuracy, especially at sub 4-bit weight precision.",
    "Moreover, the hardware needs to support operations at these precisions, to avoid dequantization before computation."
  ]
}